Unit 5, 56 Heffernan Street is a strata titled unit with a footprint of 240sqm*, comprising clear span warehouse, a retail shopfront and mezzanine storage area of 40sqm* (STCA) providing a total floor area of 280sqm*. The permitted gross floor area for the unit is 360sqm so there is potential to increase the floor area further if desired. The unit sits adjacent to 4 similar units with a common car parking. The property is located within the ‘IZ2 Industrial Mixed Used’ zone allowing for a wide range of businesses and trade uses.

CBRE offer for sale this ground floor industrial unit in North Canberra's fastest growing Industrial suburb, Mitchell. Prominently located on the corner of Lysaght and Hoskins Street, Mitchell Business Centre is a strata titled commercial centre built in circa 1991 and houses a range of occupiers.

Unit 6 is fully air conditioned (recently upgraded) with power, telephone and data outlets installed.  The unit comprises an open plan area with office/staff amenities and 2 WCs.  The unit boasts vast window space facing Hoskins Street plus fabulous internal atrium filling the centre of the building with natural light.

The unit is leased to The National Film & Sound Archive. This Commonwealth tenant has been in occupation of the premises since 1992. The lease recently expired and they have agreed a renewal on the following terms:

Lease Commencement - 15 December 2011
Lease Term - 5 years
Current Gross Rent - $110,400 +GST per annum
Rent Reviews - 3.5% per annum

45 Dacre Street is situated on the north western corner of Mitchell with exposure to Gungahlin Drive, the main arterial route connecting Gungahlin with the City, Belconnen and South Canberra. The block is one of the larger sites in Mitchell being a 1.421 hectares (14,210sqm) regular shaped corner block.

The property has been designed to form four (4) tenancies within two separate stand alone buildings of high clearance space with vehicular access.  The site incorporates extensive hardstand areas utilised for access and car parking. Security fencing and soft landscaping is provided to the site boundaries.

The building has recently been strata titled so the following 4 units are available either individually or 'in-one-line':

- Units 1 & 2 (3,454sqm*) - 10 year lease to Customs at a current passing income $433,700pa* GROSS
- Unit 3 (2,936sqm*) - Vacant (suitable for owner occupier)
- Unit 4 (2,859sqm*) - Vacant (suitable for owner occupier)

The total estimated income is $1,160,750pa* GROSS

The units are for sale by Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 7 December 2011.

To register your interest and receive further information, please contact Mark Nicholls or Andrew Stewart of CBRE, Canberra.
